Quote: LEATHERJACKET (<i>Novodon convexirostris</i>), or kokiri of the Maoris, is a small rough-skinned fish with a tiny mouth ... It is a good food fish and is sold in the Auckland market in the form of skinned fillets under the name of `cream fish'.
